ish historiography. History does not have lessons, says Alderman, but it may provide signposts, and he adds that in the case of the essays presented here “I believe there is one signpost that we would all do well to ponder: in multicultural Britain hard-working immigrants may be welcome, or they may be feared – or both. They are destined to remain not quite British, and, for better or worse, they are destined to bequeath this otherness to the generations that follow them."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh1 aAbosch, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlderman, Geoffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlderman, Geoffrey, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAppell, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCohen, Lawrence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDubnov, Arie M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEwence, Hannah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarshall, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTilles, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Backlist eBook-Package 2008-2015z978311068814640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978161811055840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781618110558423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781618110558/original  a978-3-11-068814-6  Academic Studies Press Backlist eBook-Package 2008-2015c2008d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aG